The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 14 August is 2,843 (329.1 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 10 August, there were 16 new confirmed cases (1.9 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 03 August, there were 19 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 16% (3 fewer cases).
